FBIS4-33361 "drlat108_c_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-108 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 MEXICO Baja California Authorities Investigate Entry of Weapons Baja California Authorities Investigate Entry of Weapons PA0506195294 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0430 GMT 4 Jun 94 PA0506195294 Mexico City XEW Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] The Baja California Attorney General's Office is investigating the possible entry of a large shipment of weapons through the state's border in view of the recent confiscation of 50 AK-47 rifles in Mexicali. This was disclosed by Baja California Governor Ernesto Ruffo Appel in Mexicali. [Begin Ruffo recording] Well, everyone knows that we have seized some weapons here. I think we recently seized approximately 50 of them. They were apparently part of a larger shipment. Therefore, we are investigating. [end recording] According to police, the AK-47 rifles, which were found in a clandestine workshop in Mexicali, were modified for automatic fire. Ruffo Appel said various police forces and the Army are conducting special operations in the state to detect the entry of weapons.
